title: Narrative

* This example compares ''two methods'' of hiding nodes from a TOC

* Method 1: The `toc-hide: yes` field on ''toc-1.1.1-hidden'' removes it from its parent branch automatically

* Method 2: The `exclude` parameter with `[toc-hide[yes]]` filter removes all matching tiddlers from every branch

* Both methods are shown side-by-side with a simple toc as reference

* Includes ''open/close buttons'' for programmatic branch control

