title: Output

\procedure openBranch()
<<toc-openBranch path:"/" currentTiddler:"Contents" manual:yes>>
\end

\procedure closeBranch()
<<toc-closeBranch path:"/" currentTiddler:"Contents" manual:yes>>
\end

<$button actions=<<openBranch>>>Open Tree</$button>
<$button actions=<<closeBranch>>>Close Tree</$button>

!! Method 1: toc-hide field

`toc-1.1.1-hidden` has `toc-hide: yes` — removed from its branch automatically.

<div class="tc-table-of-contents">
<<toc-selective-expandable tag:"Contents">>
</div>

!! Method 2: exclude parameter

Using `exclude:"[toc-hide[yes]]"` removes all matching tiddlers from every branch.

<div class="tc-table-of-contents">
<<toc-selective-expandable tag:"Contents" exclude:"[toc-hide[yes]]">>
</div>

!! Simple toc as reference

<div class="tc-table-of-contents">
<<toc tag:"Contents">>
</div>